## Test 3: String/Char with Escapes
## Our scanner handles 7 token types only (no strings/chars).
## These inputs test how the scanner handles unrecognized constructs.
## Strings and chars should produce ERROR tokens.

## Double-quoted strings (not in our grammar)
"hello world"
"escaped \"quote\""
"line\nbreak"
"tab\there"

## Single-quoted chars (not in our grammar)
'a'
'b'
'\n'
'\t'

## Mixed with valid tokens
Count "hello" true
42 'x' ++
(false;"test")

## Edge: quote characters standalone
"
'
